#note looks nuts since he has UNGIFTED/FATIGUED for 89, but he would then be down 16 with a 6-tile rack, which pretty much never leads to a winning endgame. Instead, he had the vision to sacrifice 68 points. He really wants to draw the X here to draw the biggest bingos possible on columnd A - stuff like FLIXWEED, EXFILLED, INFLEXED. In particular, a draw of EEILX threatens FLIXWEED 128 and FLEXTIME at 4E for 100!
>Jesse_Day: ADELOTX 2A DOX +31 433
#note first of all, I'm good. By saving my X for this turn and drawing a vowel, I can outrun the scariest bingos in the pool (LENIFIED/NINEFOLD). The question is whether I can do better on spread than just playing EXO. As it stands, he has a bingo with every tile in the bag except for the ?. He has too many bingos in too many places for me to hold back the X and save EXO for next turn. The one rack that is limited is if the E is in the bag, in which case he only has FLINTING, which I can block with EXTOLD at 4G. EXTOLD is about 3 points better than EXO because of this. However, from a game theory perspective, spread matters in this match (bigger spread starts game 7), and EXO gets me a higher spread in 7/8 pre-endgames, so possibly EXO is the right decision!!
